S; assesses the prospects of success; provides ideas for reshaping government plans and  presents an authoritative critique of a set proposals that could go badly wrong. The report will be crucial reading for politicians, civil servants and criminal justice managers. Senior probation and prison staff will find it of particular value.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh1 aAllen, Rob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAllen, Rob, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFaulkner, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHedderman, Carol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHough, Mike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHough, Mike, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLiebling, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaguire, Mike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNellis, Mike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPadel, Una, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRaine, John W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaynor, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z978311119621340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447366881423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447366881/original  a978-3-11-119621-3  Bristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995c1995d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles